The '''Heladhanavi Power Station''' is a {{Nowrap|100 [[Megawatt|MW]]}} thermal [[power station]] in [[Puttalam]], [[Sri Lanka]]. The [[fuel oil]]-run power station was commissioned in August 2004, and was operated by {{Nowrap|Heladhanavi Limited}}, a subsidiary of [[Hemas Holdings]]. It was decommissioned in 2015 by request from the [[Ministry of Power and Energy]]. The power station consisted of six {{Nowrap|[[Wartsila]] 18V46}} generation units of {{Nowrap|17 MW}} each.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Nonis|first1=Anton|title=Heladanavi to augment power supply|url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2004/07/25/new22.html|accessdate=7 November 2015|publisher=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Observer]]|date=25 July 2004}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=We decided to close down 03 thermal power generation plants that supplied electricity to the Ceylon Electricity Board|url=http://powermin.gov.lk/english/?page_id=3711|publisher=[[Ministry of Power and Energy]]|accessdate=7 November 2015|date=15 May 2015}}</ref> {{Clear}}
